1. Cloud Fundamentals
    Deployment Models: Public (AWS), Private (on-premise), and Hybrid (mix of both).
    Service Models:
      Cloud service models define what level of control and responsibility you get when using cloud computing. The three core models are IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS (with some modern extensions).


